  "description": "The last time I \u0026ldquo;installed Fennel\u0026rdquo;, it was just by \u0026ldquo;installing\u0026rdquo; TAB. This go around I\u0026rsquo;d like to more properly get it set up as accessible from my user\u0026rsquo;s shell, so I can use it like a proper interpreter across GnoponEmacs.\nSo I don\u0026rsquo;t forget, there\u0026rsquo;s this wonderful post from Andrey Listopadov about using Fennel in Emacs. I\u0026rsquo;ll be using that, the Fennel docs, and the documentation for fennel-mode to navigate through this process. My goal is to be able to use Fennel anywhere I might use another language with Org-babel, but skimming through Andrey\u0026rsquo;s blog post, I suspect I can do more than that.\n",
